# Web Dashboard Rules

## Stack

- Next.js App Router, TypeScript, server components by default
- Client components (`'use client'`) only when needed: interactivity, hooks, browser APIs
- Styling: match whatever UI library is chosen; keep consistent tokens/spacing

## Data Fetching

- Server Components fetch via `packages/fiber-rpc` in Server Actions or route handlers
- Do not expose raw node RPC to the browser — proxy through API routes
- Poll/refetch for live metrics; show stale indicators when data is old

## UX Priorities

- Dashboard first: health summary above the fold
- Every error state needs: what happened, why it matters, what to do next
- Use loading skeletons, not spinners alone, for channel/peer lists
- Format `bigint` balances with shared formatters from `packages/shared`

## Components

- Presentational vs container split where it aids clarity
- Page-level layouts in `app/`; reusable UI in `components/`
- No business logic in JSX — extract to hooks or `packages/diagnostics`
